  "instructions": [
    "Preheat your oven to 180°C (350°F). Season the duck breast with salt and pepper, and nutmeg powder. Place in a baking dish and cook for 20 minutes.",
    "While the duck cooks, sauté the onions and bell peppers in olive oil until soft and translucent.",
    "Add ginger to the pan, stir for about 30 seconds before adding broad beans. Cook for another minute or so.",
    "In a separate pan over low heat, combine heavy cream with lemon juice. Bring it to simmer without boiling.",
    "Slice cooked duck breast thinly and arrange on serving plates. Top with the bhuna vegetables, drizzle with the creamy sauce, garnish with cilantro.",
    "Serve hot as an indulgent yet low-calorie-friendly dinner option."
  ],
